\title{Zinc Database}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{"Access ZINC (230M+ purchasable compounds). Search by ZINC ID/SMILES, similarity searches, 3D-ready structures for docking, analog discovery, for virtual screening and drug discovery."}

\subtree{
\title{ZINC Database}
\subtree{
\title{Overview}
\p{ZINC is a freely accessible repository of 230M+ purchasable compounds maintained by UCSF. Search by ZINC ID or SMILES, perform similarity searches, download 3D-ready structures for docking, discover analogs for virtual screening and drug discovery.}
}

\subtree{
\title{When to Use This Skill}
\p{This skill should be used when:}

\ul{
\li{\strong{Virtual screening}: Finding compounds for molecular docking studies}
\li{\strong{Lead discovery}: Identifying commercially-available compounds for drug development}
\li{\strong{Structure searches}: Performing similarity or analog searches by SMILES}
\li{\strong{Compound retrieval}: Looking up molecules by ZINC IDs or supplier codes}
\li{\strong{Chemical space exploration}: Exploring purchasable chemical diversity}
\li{\strong{Docking studies}: Accessing 3D-ready molecular structures}
\li{\strong{Analog searches}: Finding similar compounds based on structural similarity}
\li{\strong{Supplier queries}: Identifying compounds from specific chemical vendors}
\li{\strong{Random sampling}: Obtaining random compound sets for screening}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Database Versions}
\p{ZINC has evolved through multiple versions:}

\ul{
\li{\strong{ZINC22} (Current): Largest version with 230+ million purchasable compounds and multi-billion scale make-on-demand compounds}
\li{\strong{ZINC20}: Still maintained, focused on lead-like and drug-like compounds}
\li{\strong{ZINC15}: Predecessor version, legacy but still documented}
}

\p{This skill primarily focuses on ZINC22, the most current and comprehensive version.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Access Methods}
\subtree{
\title{Web Interface}
\p{Primary access point: https://zinc.docking.org/ Interactive searching: https://cartblanche22.docking.org/}
}

\subtree{
\title{API Access}
\p{All ZINC22 searches can be performed programmatically via the CartBlanche22 API:}

\p{\strong{Base URL}: \code{\startverb https://cartblanche22.docking.org/\stopverb}}

\p{All API endpoints return data in text or JSON format with customizable fields.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Core Capabilities}
\subtree{
\title{1. Search by ZINC ID}
\p{Retrieve specific compounds using their ZINC identifiers.}

\p{\strong{Web interface}: https://cartblanche22.docking.org/search/zincid}

\p{\strong{API endpoint}:}

\pre{\startverb
curl "https://cartblanche22.docking.org/[email protected]_fields=smiles,zinc_id"
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Multiple IDs}:}

\pre{\startverb
curl "https://cartblanche22.docking.org/substances.txt:zinc_id=ZINC000000000001,ZINC000000000002&output_fields=smiles,zinc_id,tranche"
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Response fields}: \code{\startverb zinc_id\stopverb}, \code{\startverb smiles\stopverb}, \code{\startverb sub_id\stopverb}, \code{\startverb supplier_code\stopverb}, \code{\startverb catalogs\stopverb}, \code{\startverb tranche\stopverb} (includes H-count, LogP, MW, phase)}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. Search by SMILES}
\p{Find compounds by chemical structure using SMILES notation, with optional distance parameters for analog searching.}

\p{\strong{Web interface}: https://cartblanche22.docking.org/search/smiles}

\p{\strong{API endpoint}:}

\pre{\startverb
curl "https://cartblanche22.docking.org/[email protected]=4-Fadist=4"
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Parameters}:}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb smiles\stopverb}: Query SMILES string (URL-encoded if necessary)}
\li{\code{\startverb dist\stopverb}: Tanimoto distance threshold (default: 0 for exact match)}
\li{\code{\startverb adist\stopverb}: Alternative distance parameter for broader searches (default: 0)}
\li{\code{\startverb output_fields\stopverb}: Comma-separated list of desired output fields}
}

\p{\strong{Example - Exact match}:}

\pre{\startverb
curl "https://cartblanche22.docking.org/smiles.txt:smiles=c1ccccc1"
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Example - Similarity search}:}

\pre{\startverb
curl "https://cartblanche22.docking.org/smiles.txt:smiles=c1ccccc1&dist=3&output_fields=zinc_id,smiles,tranche"
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{3. Search by Supplier Codes}
\p{Query compounds from specific chemical suppliers or retrieve all molecules from particular catalogs.}

\p{\strong{Web interface}: https://cartblanche22.docking.org/search/catitems}

\p{\strong{API endpoint}:}

\pre{\startverb
curl "https://cartblanche22.docking.org/catitems.txt:catitem_id=SUPPLIER-CODE-123"
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Use cases}:}

\ul{
\li{Verify compound availability from specific vendors}
\li{Retrieve all compounds from a catalog}
\li{Cross-reference supplier codes with ZINC IDs}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{4. Random Compound Sampling}
\p{Generate random compound sets for screening or benchmarking purposes.}

\p{\strong{Web interface}: https://cartblanche22.docking.org/search/random}

\p{\strong{API endpoint}:}

\pre{\startverb
curl "https://cartblanche22.docking.org/substance/random.txt:count=100"
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Parameters}:}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb count\stopverb}: Number of random compounds to retrieve (default: 100)}
\li{\code{\startverb subset\stopverb}: Filter by subset (e.g., 'lead-like', 'drug-like', 'fragment')}
\li{\code{\startverb output_fields\stopverb}: Customize returned data fields}
}

\p{\strong{Example - Random lead-like molecules}:}

\pre{\startverb
curl "https://cartblanche22.docking.org/substance/random.txt:count=1000&subset=lead-like&output_fields=zinc_id,smiles,tranche"
\stopverb}
}
}

